            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The documents that immediately follow relate to the development of the British
                    financial crisis during the months of the Annecy meetings <pb facs="0739" n="709" xml:id="pg_709"/> (see <ref target="frus1949v04#pg_781">volume IV,
                        pages 781</ref> ff.) and the notice which was taken of it at the Third
                    Session of the Contracting Parties. The first document is of a background nature
                    and was prepared for a series of ministerial level meetings held in Washington
                    in September; see <ref target="frus1949v04#pg_822">volume IV, pages
                        822</ref>–<ref target="frus1949v04#pg_830">830</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
